data.description: Welcome to the historic charm of Paver Park Estates, where this delightful ranch home seamlessly blends mid-century Florida allure with contemporary comforts. Step inside this light, bright and colorful open-concept 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom home and experience its historic charm and recent updates. The refinished solid wood floors throughout add warmth and character to the living spaces. The updated kitchen boasts white cabinetry, granite countertops, and stainless steel appliances, creating a perfect space for culinary delights. The dining area features a wet bar and beverage fridge, as well as a wood inlaid ceiling that adds a cozy touch and ton of character. The large front bedroom boasts an en suite bathroom, wood feature wall, and glass barn door. The second bedroom offers serene views of the backyard and features wood paneling with a built-in closet organizer. The large tiled laundry room offers abundant storage space, while the attached 1-car garage provides additional storage. The outdoors beckon with a screened lanai and an expansive 10,000-square-foot backyard. The large backyard with a wooden fence is ideal for outdoor enthusiasts with boats, bikes, and RVs. Keep your favorite adventure toys in the safety and comfort of your own backyard. There is ample space for pets or children to play freely in the secure and private yard. Located in the coveted Paver Park Estates, this tranquil neighborhood, just outside downtown Sarasota, offers a haven of sprawling oaks, creating canopy-covered streets that offer old-Florida beauty, privacy and seclusion. This home is close to the beautiful Payne Park with easy access to all downtown Sarasota has to offer. Ride your bike on the Legacy Trail, to the downtown Saturday Farmers Market, through Towles Court Artist Colony, and over to Marina Jack’s. Lido Beach and St. Armands are only 5 miles away! This community is a sound investment, rapidly appreciating in value with updates and new construction. With no Homeowners Association fees, CDD fees, or deed restrictions, this property offers flexibility for year-round, seasonal, or rental use. Immerse yourself in the unique charm of a historic home with a story to tell!
